            <ce:table xmlns="http://www.elsevier.com/xml/common/cals/dtd" id="tbl0010" colsep="0" rowsep="0" frame="topbot">
               <ce:label>Table 2</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0025">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0025" view="all">AICc tables of mixed models of fragmentation effects on alpha functional diversity. The response variable was the standardized effect size (SES) of two functional diversity metrics. Marginal r<ce:sup loc="post">2</ce:sup> corresponds to the goodness-of-fit of just the fixed effects, while conditional r<ce:sup loc="post">2</ce:sup> corresponds to the overall goodness-of-fit of the model. Bolded predictor variables indicate a significant statistical effect. P-values indicate whether a model was significantly better than the null model according to a likelihood ratio test.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
