               <ce:label>Table 3</ce:label>
               <ce:caption id="cap0030">
                  <ce:simple-para id="sp0030" view="all">Beta diversity partitioning of taxonomic and functional diversity. Sample sizes refer to the number of species included in each community subset. Overall beta diversity is calculated across all sites (<ce:italic>N</ce:italic> = 14 transects). Partitioned diversity represents the proportion of beta diversity attributable to nested species loss (β<ce:inf loc="post">JNE</ce:inf>) and species turnover (β<ce:inf loc="post">JTU</ce:inf>) across the fragment size gradient.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:caption>
